com.skype.tutorial.step4
Class Tutorial_4

java.lang.Object
  com.skype.tutorial.step4.Tutorial_4

public class Tutorial_4
extends java.lang.Object

Getting Started With SkypeKit: Tutorial Application, Step 4. This example illustrates a simple SkypeKit-based program that:

  1. Takes a Skype Name, password, and optional AppToken path name as command-line arguments
  2. Initiates login for that user
  3. Waits until the login process is complete
  4. Accesses the user’s Contacts
  5. Lists the display name of each Contact
  6. Waits for and displays online status updates until the user presses ENTER to quit
  7. Initiates logout
  8. Waits until logout is complete
  9. Cleans up and exits

Since:
1.0
Author:
Andrea Drane (ported/refactored from existing C++ tutorial code)
